Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light orange-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Antigonos. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0317.25.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0765)
